 -- Function: function_convert (CONVERTERS, EXPR)
     Apply one or more function-conversion rules to the expression EXPR.
     The argument CONVERTERS is either a single conversion rule 'f => g'
     or a list of such rules.

     A conversion rule has the form 'f => g', where 'f' is the source
     function and 'g' is either a target function name or a lambda
     expression.

     The operator '=>' indicates a _semantic_ conversion, not a literal
     renaming.  For example, the rule 'sinc => sin' does not replace the
     symbol 'sinc' by 'sin'.  Instead, it applies the 'sinc(x) =
     sin(x)/x'; specifically
          (%i1) function_convert('sinc => 'sin, sinc(x) + 1);
                                            sin(x)
          (%o1)                             ────── + 1
                                              x

     Users may also supply an explicit conversion by giving a lambda
     expression on the right-hand side.  For example:

          (%i2) function_convert('erfc => lambda([q], 1-erf(q)), erfc(x)^2);
                                                       2
          (%o2)                            (1 - erf(x))

     Multiple conversions may be given in a Maxima list; they are
     applied from left to right.

     *Example*

          (%i3) function_convert(['sinc => 'sin,'sin => 'exp], sinc(x));
                                          %i x     - %i x
                                       (%e     - %e      ) %i
          (%o3)                      - ──────────────────────
                                                2 x

 -- Function: list_converters [name_1, name_2, ...]

     Return a list of all registered function converters known to
     'function_convert'.  In addition to returning this list, each
     converter is printed as a pair 'FROM => TO' followed by a short
     description taken from the converter's docstring.

     When called with no arguments, 'list_converters' returns the full
     set of converters.  When one or more names are supplied, only those
     converters whose source function matches one of the given names are
     returned.

          (%i1) list_converters();
          sinc => sin : Convert sinc(x) into sin(x)/x.
          csc  => sin : Convert csc(x) into 1/sin(x).
          cos  => exp : Convert cos(x) to exponential form.
          tan  => sin : Convert tan(x) into sin(x)/cos(x).
          sin  => exp : Convert sin(x) to exponential form.
          (%o1) [sinc => sin, csc => sin, cos => exp, tan => sin, sin => exp]

          (%i2) list_converters(sinc, tan);
          sinc => sin : Convert sinc(x) into sin(x)/x.
          tan  => sin : Convert tan(x) into sin(x)/cos(x).
          (%o2) [sinc => sin, tan => sin]

     The list of converters is maintained internally and entries appear
     in an unspecified order.

     'function_convert'.




